                <head>No. 576.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Cushing</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 27, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 61.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of your interesting
                    dispatch of the 30th ultimo, No. 66, in relation to the possibility of European
                    intervention in the affairs of Spain. It confirms accounts which have reached
                    this country of atrocities in warfare which seem incredible in the nineteenth
                    century, which are without excuse or palliation, and a continuance of which
                    would be degrading to human nature.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
